16:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Suno is best suited for creating music without instruments, content creators needing custom music, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Voicemod, meanwhile, shines for gamers and streamers, fun voice effects, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Suno describes itself as \"Create full songs with AI from a text prompt.\" Voicemod, established in 2014, positions itself as \"Real-time AI voice changer for gaming and streaming.\" With 9 years between them, Voicemod brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Suno offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
17:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Suno** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 6.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Voicemod is a poor choice — far from it. Voicemod excels in its own right, particularly for gamers and streamers and fun voice effects.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value incredibly easy to use, go with Suno. If real-time voice changing matters more to you, Voicemod is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
